headline: Nasdaq Crosses US$5b Revenue As AI Growth Meets Valuation Questions
summary: Nasdaq reports annual net revenue above $5b for the first time. Management attributes the milestone to organic growth, wider use of AI tools and new fintech offerings. Nasdaq also secures regulatory approvals that expand its trading capabilities, including in digital assets. For investors watching NasdaqGS:NDAQ, this revenue marker highlights how far the business has moved beyond its roots as a US equities exchange. headline: NDAQ Q4 Deep Dive: Solutions Revenue and AI Initiatives Drive Robust Growth Amid Margin Compression
summary: Global exchange operator Nasdaq (NASDAQ:NDAQ) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 13.4% year on year to $1.39 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.96 per share was 4.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
